</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
3.3-3.6 mm long (mean = 3.48 mm; n = 4); 2.83-3.0
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide. This species is distinguished by the posterolateral extensions of elytra short, less than the width of apical emargination, and declivity shallowly excavated; declivity clearly, confusedly punctate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. shoreae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="shoreae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. shoreae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is distinguished by the punctation of the declivity.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
